# Part 1 - Security Architecture

## Purpose

Security is a platform capability.

Security is never an afterthought.

Every architectural decision must preserve

- Confidentiality
- Integrity
- Availability
- Accountability
- Tenant Isolation
- Least Privilege

Security is everyone's responsibility.

---

## Security Philosophy

Business Capability

↓

Security Requirements

↓

Architecture

↓

Microservices

↓

Implementation

↓

Verification

↓

Monitoring

Security is designed into the platform.

It is never added after implementation.

---

## Zero Trust Architecture

Never trust

External Users

Internal Users

Microservices

Plugins

Networks

AI Models

External APIs

Every request must be

Authenticated

Authorized

Validated

Audited

