## Authentication

Authentication proves

Who the user is.

Supported mechanisms

JWT

OAuth2

OpenID Connect

API Keys (Internal Integrations)

Anonymous access is prohibited unless explicitly approved.

---

## Authorization

Authorization determines

What the authenticated user may do.

Authorization is enforced using

RBAC

Permissions

Tenant Context

Business Rules

Never rely only on frontend authorization.

---

## Role-Based Access Control

Permissions are assigned to Roles.

Roles are assigned to Users.

Business Services evaluate permissions before executing business operations.

Never hardcode permissions.

---

## Tenant Isolation

Every authenticated request resolves

tenant_id

organization_id

user_id

roles

permissions

Every service validates tenant ownership before accessing data.

Cross-tenant access is prohibited.

---

## API Gateway Security

Every external request enters through the API Gateway.

Gateway responsibilities

Authentication

JWT Validation

Rate Limiting

Tenant Resolution

Correlation ID

Request Logging

Security Headers

Gateway never performs business logic.

---

## Service-to-Service Security

Internal communication must use

Authenticated identities

JWT propagation

Internal authorization

Correlation IDs

Future architecture may introduce mTLS.

Services never trust internal traffic implicitly.

---

## Plugin Security

Every plugin executes within defined permissions.

Industry Plugins

May access only their own business capabilities.

Capability Plugins

May access only approved platform services.

Plugins never bypass platform security.

---

## AI Security

AI Service must protect

Prompt Templates

Knowledge Base

Embeddings

Provider Credentials

Inference History

Token Usage

AI outputs are treated as untrusted input.

Business Services validate AI recommendations.

