---

## Mandatory Rules

### MUST

- Authenticate every protected request.
- Authorize every business operation.
- Resolve tenant context before business logic.
- Store secrets in Secret Manager or Vault.
- Validate all user input.
- Sanitize all outputs.
- Protect S3 with private buckets and pre-signed URLs.
- Encrypt sensitive data in transit and at rest.
- Audit security-sensitive operations.
- Search the repository before creating new security components.

### MUST NOT

- Hardcode secrets.
- Trust client input.
- Trust AI output.
- Trust internal network traffic.
- Expose stack traces.
- Log passwords, tokens, or secrets.
- Share authentication logic across services without governance.
- Allow cross-tenant access.
- Disable authorization checks.
- Duplicate security implementations.

---

